not going to pay for shipping to return an incorrect item, and would like

willing to be patient at first due to the holiday season and postal strike
here in Canada, but this has been going on for far too long.  I will gladly
return the unopened wireless earbud headphones, providing that your company
pays for shipping, but I would expect to receive either the treadmill that
I paid for, or a full refund.

John Hamilton

Order 2231

I have written several emails to you regarding Order 2231 that I placed and
Solopopgo confirmed on Tuesday, November 6, 2018 at 11:23 PM.  The tracking
number you sent is not a number that can be tracked via United States
Postal Service (USPS) in spite of the tracking information it gives.  I
personally went to our local office and asked them to track the number you
referenced, UE685135308YP.  It is not in USPS system. If it cannot be
tracked in the USPS system, then it is a false number and the tracking
information given is false too.  If the post office would have delivered it
to me, or held it at the post office in Crown Point, as your tracking
information says, they would have a record of it.  Again, the tracking
number you supplied is incorrect and the tracking information attached to
that number is also false.   Basically, this looks and smells like a scam.
You have taken my $139.99 USD; you have not delivered the product ordered,
and you have supplied false information as to the shipping and delivery of
the product.  The order was never delivered to me or to the post office
here.   I expect a refund of 139.99 United States Dollars.  Your company,
or companies, have not kept your part of the agreement, as agreed to in the
confirmation received from Solopopgo and furthermore the shipping
information you have supplied is false and deceptive.  I will appreciate
your quick response regarding the refund and the money returned to me via a
credit.  Please let me know when I can expect the refund.  I trust that you
did not intend to commit fraud and so will correct this situation by
refunding my payment of $139.99 USD.

Gayle MacBride

Do you realize that a company that makes a walking pad has a Facebook page on which many of the people Solopopgo has screwed over in exactly the same way it has me are posting about you? Angry customers complaining about this shoddy treatment and asking about legal action. People are HURT. 

Your note says I should be patient while you “deal my question.”

WHAT? You steal from and lie to me and others and have the audacity to ask for patience?  

All you are supposed to do is send the product for which I paid and your company sent false shipping information, which is a serious crime with hefty fines when committed on this scale. 

I want the product for which I paid. 

But it seems unlikely that the product is even exists.  It seems likely that Solopopgo is a scam.

A company that takes $140 from a number of customers and goes to the trouble of sending those customers a totally unrelated and utterly worthless product is run by people who are immoral, unethical, soulless and arrogant criminals, possibly very stupid criminals since the expense to ship trash cut your profits.

I am generally a forgiving person but this is outrageous.

Think about your personal role in perpetuating this evil. Have you no shame, no self-respect? I guess not.

I hope you and every person who is responsible for this scam suffer severe consequences. 

Your customer service is horrible.

There is definitely a communication problem here.  Evidently you did not
read my last email.  The link you just sent is the one you sent before.  I
have looked at it.  This package was not delivered to my mail box nor was
it delivered to my house.  My mail box is large enough for letters, but a
60 pound package would could not be delivered there.  I took this tracking
information to the Crown Point Post Office.  They have no record of the
package coming in and they cannot locate the tracking number you gave in
their records.  So-- that package was NOT delivered to me.  Therefore I
will need a refund of $139.99 US dollars for the item I ordered, paid for
but have not received.  I'm also filing a claim with the United State Post
Office, so that they can attempt to track the item by the tracking number
you gave.  Please advise when I will receive the refund of $139.99 US
dollars for a product I did not receive.  I expect an honest response.

Gayle MacBride

Below is my previous email to you.  Please read it and respond
appropriately.
*I have just come from our local post office.  They tried to track the
shipment by the tracking number UE685135308YP on the tracking information I
got from clicking on the link www.oiele.com/tracking/express
<http://www.oiele.com/tracking/express>.  The post office could not pull up
this tracking number on their system. There is no evidence that the package
was ever delivered to this post office, USPS, in Crown Point, Indiana. It
appears that the tracking information connected to this tracking number is
in error or false.  I have not received the item I ordered, our post office
did not received it (in spite of the tracking information, which cannot be
verified).  I will be filing a claim with the USPS.  Furthermore, the
tracking information says I requested that the item be delivered to the
local post office.   I did not request that it be delivered to the post
office.  I requested it be delivered to my home address.  This has not
happened, and there is no record that the package was even delivered to the
local post office nor have you provided accurate information as to the
location of the package.  Since you have not been able to deliver the
package to my address, and the package cannot be located, I will need a
refund for $139.99, the amount paid for order 3341, 1 - folded fitness
equipment.  Again, the refund is because the equipment was never delivered
to me.  *

shipment by the tracking number UE685135308YP on the tracking information I
got from clicking on the link www.oiele.com/tracking/express.  The post
office could not pull up this tracking number on their system. There is no
evidence that the package was ever delivered to this post office, USPS, in
Crown Point, Indiana. It appears that the tracking information connected to
this tracking number is in error or false.  I have not received the item I
ordered, our post office did not received it (in spite of the tracking
information, which cannot be verified).  I will be filing a claim with the
USPS.  Furthermore, the tracking information says I requested that the item
be delivered to the local post office.   I did not request that it be
delivered to the post office.  I requested it be delivered to my home
address.  This has not happened, and there is no record that the package
was even delivered to the local post office nor have you provided accurate
information as to the location of the package.  Since you have not been
able to deliver the package to my address, and the package cannot be
located, I will need a refund for $139.99, the amount paid for order 3341,
1 - folded fitness equipment.  Again, the refund is because the equipment
was never delivered to me.

Gayle MacBride

I ordred a folded fitness equipment folding treadmill November 13,2018 order number 11593.  You billed me twice for this merchandise on my card on November 13, 2018. I contacted you on this day and said i didn't know if the first order went threw because i did not get a reply and told you i only wanted one to please cancel the first order.  You agreed and said you fixed this. Now today December 30th I get an email that it was delivered on December 17th. 2018.   The only item that was delivered to my address was a pair of ear buds. No treadmill.  I have cameras all over my house and went back and looked at the cameras and nothing was delivered to my home, and a folding treadmill does not fold up enough to fit in my mail box.  I did report this to my credit card company.  I was really looking forward to this treadmill, told everyone i know about it. But looks like i should have read the reviews before i ordered it.  The reviews say it is a great item if you get it.  The company that is shipping the item is fraud, they do not ship items and charge twice.   I do hope this is not true. please refund my order for one and ship the item or refund both fees and ship nothing.


Susan Magner

Brick, NJ 008724

letter and did not address any of my questions or comments and is of no

I.  Your first option (1. Track your package. You can click here and enter
your email address: www.oiele.com/tracking/express)  requires downloading
an invasive software onto my computer.  This I will not do.  I will need
you to track it and inform me of the shipping status or give me a link that
works and doesn't require a download.
2.  In your original email you listed three other options for tracking the
shipment which either gave incorrect information or could not locate the
tracking number.
     Option 1.  This option said that the package was delivered on December
3, 2018.  It was not delivered to my address which was the shipping address
on the order.
     Option 2 and Option 3: Neither option could find the tracking number.
3.  Refund:  I do not have the product.  It was never delivered.  Therefore
I cannot return it.  There seems to be a problem with your identifying the
status of the shipment and letting me know where it is in the shipping
process.  Again, your option for tracking is unacceptable as it requires
downloading an invasive software.  It may be in transit.  All I want is
accurate tracking information without having to download an invasive
program.

So please understand.  This order was placed in October.  It is now the end
of December and I have not received the product.  Your company cannot or
will not give me tracking information I can use, that will not put
questionable software on my computer, or provide me with a tracking options
that works.  If this confusion, misinformation and unacceptable tracking
program continues with no results, I will ask for a refund.  The problem is
that I HAVE NOT RECEIVED THE ITEM ORDERED, and you have not or cannot
provide me with good tracking information including a safe tracking
program.  The link you recommend doesn't appear to be a safe option.

At this point, the order appears to be a failed effort.  I have paid for a
product that you have not delivered to me.  In an attempt to resolve this,
please provide me with a safe option for tracking.  Do not send this link (
www.oiele.com/tracking/express) as it is invasive and not safe.  I do not
trust it and I do not want it on my computer.  You could locate the
shipment and let me know where it is, how it will be delivered and when it
will be delivered and who will deliver it.  If a local company (UPS, FedEx)
will deliver, I may be able to track it through them.  Please let me know.
If you cannot provide accurate information and a good estimate of delivery,
then I will request a refund because you have not delivered the product or
given me good, safe tracking information.  I expect to hear from you with
accurate meaningful information-- please look into this problem and do not
send you formula response.  It only tells me you have not made an attempt
to do anything to resolve this issue.

I hope to hear from you soon.

Gayle MacBride

Hello,

This message is regarding order # 1721. 
PLEASE, read my whole email.  

I DID NOT receive the item I ordered (compact treadmill). I instead received a pair of generic Apple/iPhone earbuds. According to social media, I know I am not alone in this. 

Since it is still within your arbitrary “ ‘14 days’ after delivery return policy,” despite NOT receiving the correct item, 

******I request a return/refund.******

 Be aware that I also initiated fraud services from my bank, Bank of America, on 12/12/2018 due to receiving the INCORRECT item. I know I am not alone in this. 

I understand that I received a manufactured tracking email that mirrors the exact same route for the original number that was the earbuds. Also, the United States Post Office does not have the tracking information for ‘UE687576033YP’ in any form. They only have tracking information for ‘LN360462365KR’ which serves as evidence that the tracking information for ‘UE687576033YP’ on your ‘Tracking More/ Yanwen Tracking’ website is COMPLETELY FALSIFIED.

This message is regarding order # 1721.

I originally sent this second email to which you’ve responded after receiving what I believe was an INCORRECT item from your company. I received a package of generic ‘iPhone’ earbuds instead of the item I actually ordered. I ordered a compact treadmill type item.

I’m almost certain this item (generic iPhone earbuds) is from your company because I peeled back many of the numerous labels on it and one has the original tracking number I was provided. 

I was originally provided tracking number: UE687576033YP and this item was received under tracking number: LN360462365KR. According to the United States Postal Service, this item originated from Korea. I further believe this is an incorrect product from your company because I haven’t made any other foreign purchases in over 70 days.

According to social media websites, I am not the only purchaser who has received earbuds or another INCORRECT product in lieu of the original purchase. 

** I request that you initiate a refund.**

Again, please assist and help correct this error. I have taken photographs of everything and I am also making sure to send and document that I sent these messages within your company’s specified return window of ‘14 days after item receipt.’

** I request that you initiate a refund.**

Also, be advised that my bank’s fraud department has been alerted.

Again, this purchase was made from solopopgo.com and I am writing regarding order #1721.

Sincerely,

Jenna Patskin

Compatible with ebay / aliexpress / magento: with your ebay,aliexpress,magento account bounding to trackingmore,our system will collect the data together , so you can check out the waybill information in one place.2.muti-language support: support sixteen different languages,so it's convenient for users from different countries.
About YANWENYANWEN International Logistics   Department was founded in 1998. With sufficient experience and professional   qualities of international logistics and international trade, we can provide you  with international logistics services, such as import and export agent,   international air and ocean freight forwarder and customs clearance. For the   different needs of customers, we endeavor to provide customers with the overall   plan and comprehensive logistics solutions, with the purpose of improving the   efficiency of logistic management, reducing the operating cost, and winning a   competitive advantage for the customer. At present, the International Logistics   Department has owned a well-established international network which is able to   be operated in 123 countries worldwidely.                    As an outstanding logistic   service supplier, we have provided our services for many large multi-national   companies, and gradually completed the change from a freight forwarder to a real   global logistics service supplier.

Well, at least that tracking number worked. I just checked and saw that I
got something in the mail today. However, that is *NOT* what I ordered. I
ordered two folding treadmill/walking devices (you called it "*Folded
fitness equipment*.") You can see that screenshot of a person walking on it
in the original email confirmation I got when I made my purchase.

[image: image.png]

What I got today was a single fitness tracking band that you wear on your
wrist. What happened to the two treadmills? That is nothing close to what I
had ordered and certainly not worth the $279.98 that I was charged.

[image: IMG_20181213_221140.jpg]
[image: IMG_20181213_221153.jpg]

So, this all got me thinking and I decided to look around a bit more. After
digging into this further, I see that I have been the victim of a SCAM and
you should be ashamed of yourself for duping well-intended consumers like
myself with crap like this.

https://shop.walkingpad.com/pages/name-and-shame
https://noscams.info/a-new-type-scam-on-facebook/

I will be submitting a chargeback on my credit card and taking further
action against you to keep others from getting scammed by your unethical
behavior. I cannot believe that I've spent the past several days thinking
that you were actually a legit company. You're nothing but a fraud.

Shame on you... :-(
